    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team concludes that the CFD hemolysis model demonstrates sufficient credibility for regulatory submission. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was completed and hemolysis predictions trend below the clinical threshold across the evaluated operating points. The team judges the overall evidence package to support a High assurance level based on the UQ results and the partial validation comparisons performed. Unassessed factors are noted as future work items but are not considered disqualifying for the current submission cycle.",
